   "source": [
    "# FD calculation of radioactive decay\n",
    "We will solve for radioactive using explicit and implicit FD schemes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5ee9b051",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Load libraries and set resolution of output figures"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "19ea4f88",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib as mpl\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "mpl.rcParams['figure.dpi']= 300"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ada10b55",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Define physics constants, here we use arbitrary values without any physical meaning"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "3b5307f1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "c0      = 1      # initial concentration\n",
    "k       = 0.1    # decay constant"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bb82a90d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Setup numerics"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 69,
   "id": "fe055a8a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dt      = 50                            # time step\n",
    "steps   = 11                            # number of time steps\n",
    "Cana    = np.zeros(steps)               # analytical solution\n",
    "Cana[0] = c0                            # initial condition\n",
    "\n",
    "Cexp    = Cana.copy()                   # make a copy\n",
    "Cimp    = Cana.copy()\n",
    "Ccen    = Cana.copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "Time    = np.linspace(0, (steps-1)*dt, steps)  # time stepping, and Time vector"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "aa683774",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Perform calculation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 70,
   "id": "c9067039",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# hide\n",
    "for n in range(0,len(Cana)-1): \n",
    "    \n",
    "    Cana[n+1] = np.exp(-k*Time[n+1])            #analytical\n",
    "    Cexp[n+1] = Cexp[n]*(1-k*dt)                #explicit\n",
    "    Cimp[n+1] = Cimp[n]/(1+k*dt)                #implicit\n",
    "    Ccen[n+1] = Ccen[n]*(1-k*dt*0.5)/(1+k*dt*0.5) #centered"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 71,
   "id": "e2d0b094",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# write update rules for the explicit and implicit cases!\n",
    "# Bonus: write an update rule that uses the concentration at the middle of the time step\n",
    "#for n in range(0,len(Cana)-1): \n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Cana[n+1] = np.exp(-k*Time[n+1])            #analytical\n",
    "    # Cexp[n+1] = ???\n",
    "    # Cimp[n+1] = ???"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a5566adc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Plot different solutions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 72,
   "id": "4bd659b3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<function matplotlib.pyplot.show(close=None, block=None)>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 72,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 3000x1500 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# First set up the figure, the axis, and the plot element we want to animate\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))\n",
    "fig.clf()\n",
    "ax  = plt.axes(xlim=(0, dt*(steps-1)), ylim=(-c0, c0))\n",
    "line, = ax.plot([], [], lw=1)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Time')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Concentration')\n",
    "plt.plot(Time, Cana, label='Analytical solution')\n",
    "plt.plot(Time, Cexp, label='Explicit solution')\n",
    "plt.plot(Time, Cimp, label='Implicit solution')\n",
    "plt.plot(Time, Ccen, label='Centered solution')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show"
   ]
  },
